Author-Name: Geoffroy de Clippel
Title: Behavioral Implementation
Abstract: Implementation theory assumes that participants' choices are rational,
in the sense of being consistent with the maximization of a context-
independent preference. The paper investigates implementation
under complete information when individuals'  choices need not be
rational. 
