Author-Name: Petra Moser
Author-Name: Alessandra Voena
Author-Name: Fabian Waldinger
Title: German Jewish ?migr?s and US Invention
Abstract: Historical accounts suggest that Jewish ?migr?s from Nazi Germany
revolutionized US science. To analyze the ?migr?s' effects on chemical
innovation in the United States, we compare changes in patenting
by US inventors in research fields of ?migr?s with fields of other
German chemists. Patenting by US inventors increased by 31 percent
in ?migr? fields. Regressions which instrument for ?migr? fields with
pre-1933 fields of dismissed German chemists confirm a substantial
increase in US invention. Inventor-level data indicate that ?migr?s
encouraged innovation by attracting new researchers to their fields,
rather than by increasing the productivity of incumbent inventors.
